<html>
<body>

<br><strong>Add an OAI Harvester Object</strong><br>

<p>This is a OAI Namespace object. In some cases users will be able to choose to add this type of namespace. In all cases it will be used as a helper during certain OAI server requests.</p><br>

<form action="manage_addOAIExistNamespace">

<table>
<tr><th align="left" valign="top">Namespace URL:</th>
<td><input name="ns_namespace" size=50 value="http://www.openarchives.org/OAI/2.0/oai_dc/"></td>
</tr>

<tr><th align="left" valign="top">Shortname:</th>
<td><input name="ns_shortname" size=50 value="OAI Dublin Core"></td>
</tr>

<tr><th align="left" valign="top">Prefix:</th>
<td><input name="ns_prefix" size=50 value="oai_dc"></td>
</tr>

<tr><th align="left" valign="top">Root Node:</th>
<td><input name="ns_rootNode" size=50 value="dc"></td>
</tr>

<tr><th align="left" valign="top">Schema URL:</th>
<td><input name="ns_schema" size=50 value="http://www.openarchives.org/OAI/2.0/oai_dc.xsd"></td>
</tr>

<tr><th align="left" valign="top">Description:</th>
<td><textarea name="ns_description" cols=35 rows=5>Open Archives Initiative metadata format based on Dublin Core</textarea></td>
</tr>

<tr><td colspan=2 align="left"><strong>eXist Configuration Part</strong></td></tr>

<tr><th align="left" valign="top">Namespace Declaration</th>
<td>
<textarea name="ns_nsDeclaration:lines" cols="50" rows="3" >
</textarea>
</td>
</tr>

<tr><th align="left" valign="top">Possible node root storage</th>
<td><input name="ns_possibleRootNode" size=50 value=""> (must be prefixed like the ns edit before) -- the first is use for eXist storage</td>
</tr>

<tr><th align="left" valign="top">Id ressource path</th>
<td><input name="ns_idPath" size=50 value=""> (indicate from the root node, use * as prefix for larger search)</td>
</tr>


<tr><td colspan=2 align="left"><input type="submit" value="submit"></td></tr>

</table>
</form>

</body>
</html>